            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-accent mb-3">🇩🇪 Germany</p>
            <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">The Arbeitsschutzgesetz (ArbSchG) mandates a Gefährdungsbeurteilung for every workplace, including home offices. The Bildschirmarbeitsverordnung sets specific ergonomic standards for screen-based work. The documentation trail required to defend against a claim is exacting. Most SMEs have neither.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-sm p-6 border border-brand-border shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-accent mb-3">🇨🇭 Switzerland</p>
            <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">The Arbeitsgesetz and its implementing ordinance ArGV 3 set binding ergonomic requirements for all workplaces. SUVA, Switzerland's national accident insurer, actively audits compliance. Employers who cannot demonstrate a structured risk assessment face both regulatory and insurance consequences.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-sm p-6 border border-brand-border shadow-sm">
