            <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">Austria's ArbeitnehmerInnenschutzgesetz (ASchG) and the 2021 Homeoffice-Gesetz explicitly extend ergonomic obligations to home office environments. Employer-provided equipment must meet defined ergonomic standards, and a documented risk assessment is required for every workstation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-sm p-6 border border-brand-border shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-accent mb-3">🇬🇧 UK &amp; 🇮🇪 Ireland</p>
            <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">The UK's DSE Regulations and Ireland's Safety, Health and Welfare at Work Act both require documented risk assessments for every screen user, including remote workers. The duty of care is identical for home and office environments. Insurers are increasingly requesting documented evidence before renewing employer liability policies.</p>
